description: Florida has the second highest population enrolled in the individual market, with two million people purchasing insurance through HealthCare.gov (Kaiser Family Foundation, 2016). The state is ranked 11th in the country for diabetes prevalence, and has a diverse population in the individual market (The State of Obesity Project, 2016). Endocrinologists are specialists trained to diagnose and treat diabetes. Use this map to explore the availability of endocrinologists in marketplace plans.
dataSources: Provider Data: CCIIO Health Insurance Exchange Public Use Files, 2018.
subtitle: All Endocrinologists in Florida marketplace plans
